self.philbrown.AbLE.annotations
Annotation Type Getter

@Target(value=FIELD)
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Getter

This annotation deprecates InstanceMethod by providing its functionality in addition to passing parameters to the method. For example, the below will call the method public ? getStuff(0, "tag1") and place the returned value as the value of the variable stuff.

 @Getter
 public static Object stuff = new Object[]{0, "tag1"};

Author:
Phil Brown

Optional Element Summary
 java.lang.String methodName
          Sets the method name.
 

methodName

public abstract java.lang.String methodName
Sets the method name. This is optional, as generally the variable name is used to get the method name by prepending "get", however for methods with other names (such as "findViewById"), this is a nice attribute to have.

Returns:
the name of the method to call.
Default:
""
